Description: Fragment flaked from body, probably of Attic black-figure painted pottery amphora. Charioteer standing beyond team of horses. White on chiton.
Bibliographic references: CVA British Museum 8 / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain 13, British Museum 8 (Pl. GB 608, 28)
Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 71)
